## üí° Clinical Notes & Commentary

### Traditional Understanding
"Preserve the Metal" refers to nourishing the lung system (metal element). Classic formula for lung and kidney yin deficiency with chronic respiratory symptoms. The lily bulb (Bai He) is the signature herb for lung yin nourishment and respiratory protection.

### Modern Pharmacology
Research shows anti-inflammatory, antitussive, and lung-protective effects. Bai He contains saponins with respiratory benefits. Studies demonstrate efficacy in chronic cough, COPD, and post-infectious respiratory conditions.

### Clinical Experience
Essential formula for chronic respiratory conditions with yin deficiency. Particularly effective for healthcare workers, teachers, and singers with vocal strain. Often used long-term for lung protection and chronic respiratory support.

### Dosage & Administration
**Standard Dose**: Decoct above doses twice daily, or 6-9g granules twice daily
**Preparation**: Standard decoction, don't overcook yin-nourishing herbs
**Timing**: Between meals, can take with honey for throat coating
**Duration**: 2-8 weeks for acute cough, longer for chronic conditions

